world's youngest
country, founded in 2011, is in
freefall.

23:00.446 --> 23:05.584 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Three of its six years in
existence have been
spent fighting a civil war that
has left tens

23:05.618 --> 23:07.186 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of thousands dead.

23:07.219 --> 23:11.690 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Now the ravages of that war have
led to a
manmade famine.

23:11.724 --> 23:17.463 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Last week, the United Nations
reported that
7.5 million people there are in
need of assistance.

23:17.496 --> 23:22.067 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
From South Sudan, John Ray of
Independent
Television News brings us this
report.

23:22.101 --> 23:25.371 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And a warning: Viewers may find
some of the
images upsetting.

23:25.404 --> 23:34.446 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN RAY: Of South Sudan's many
torments,
hunger has become the greatest
terror of all.

23:34.480 --> 23:41.553 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It is a horror written in the
flesh and bones
of this little boy.

23:41.587 --> 23:44.923 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It has drawn the strength from
his limbs and
the life from his eyes.

23:44.957 --> 23:53.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
His name is Khamis, 2 years old,
but weaker
than a newborn baby.

23:53.899 --> 24:00.005 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
His mother has lost one child to
sickness,
lost family to war, and now
starvation threatens

24:00.039 --> 24:01.307 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
her son.

24:01.340 --> 24:05.778 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LOMO LATABO, Mother (through
translator):
There is no food.

24:05.811 --> 24:08.047 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Anything we can find, we will
try to eat.

24:08.080 --> 24:09.948 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We find grass, we will eat it.

24:09.982 --> 24:11.850 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That's just the way it is for us
now.

24:11.884 --> 24:16.889 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JOHN RAY: The red warning signs
are everywhere.

24:16.922 --> 24:23.862 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
At this screening center out in
the countryside,
we're told four out of every 10
children are

24:23.896 --> 24:25.731 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
severely acutely malnourished.

24:25.764 --> 24:32.304 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In language any parent would
understand, they
risk starving to death.

24:32.338 --> 24:37.876 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, with every exhausted step,
South Sudan
moves from the brink of genocide
into the

24:37.910 --> 24:39.745 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
arms of famine.

24:39.778 --> 24:44.116 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
For many days and many miles,
they have trekked
across a sand-blown wasteland in
search of

24:44.149 --> 24:47.686 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
something to eat and somewhere
safe to stay.

24:47.720 --> 24:54.760 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
