policy and
are not corrected by the
so-called immune

28:10.923 --> 28:16.395 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
system of democracy, a free
press and a free
democratic discourse.

28:16.428 --> 28:21.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I think we have a huge
systemic problem
that we have largely ignored.

28:21.633 --> 28:26.772 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
When our founders created
America, it was
in the age of the printing
press, when individuals

28:26.805 --> 28:29.274 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
could freely join the
conversation.

28:29.308 --> 28:35.647 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that robust, democratic
dialogue more
often than not lifted up the
best available

28:35.681 --> 28:39.985 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
evidence and asserted what was
more likely
to be true than not.

28:40.018 --> 28:46.191 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Now we have things that are
obviously false,
leading us to war, leading us to
deny people

28:46.224 --> 28:49.328 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
health care, leading us to
ignore the climate
crisis.

28:49.361 --> 28:52.397 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We have to restore the integrity
of the democratic
conversation.

28:52.431 --> 28:56.101 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, back when
you first wrote
the book, you were pretty
optimistic, you

28:56.134 --> 29:01.273 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
wrote, that the Internet would
be an open
-- an opportunity for the kind
of discourse

29:01.306 --> 29:02.341 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
that you would like to see.

29:02.374 --> 29:03.342 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
AL GORE: Yes.

29:03.375 --> 29:04.576 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Has it turned out
that way?

29:04.610 --> 29:07.112 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
AL GORE: Not as quickly as I had
hoped, that's
for sure.

29:07.145 --> 29:09.481 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I still do have hope, however.

29:09.514 --> 29:15.320 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If you look at the way all of
the new reform
movements dedicated to the
public interest

29:15.354 --> 29:21.026 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
are living and thriving on the
Internet, I
do think there is still some
considerable

29:21.059 --> 29:27.766 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
hope that the full participation
of individuals
in that conversation of
democracy can once

29:27.799 --> 29:30.836 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
again restore the integrity of
the way our
democracy works.

29:30.869 --> 29:34.139 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, you write
about that
in the book, in the update, but
you also say

29:34.172 --> 29:38.977 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that you think it's wrong to go
after President
Trump as the principal cause of
the.

29:39.011 --> 29:43.682 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, as you well know, there are
others out
there who are saying he is,
because -- a principal

29:43.715 --> 29:50.222 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
cause, because of the language
we have heard
from him about how many people
showed up at

29:50.255 --> 29:53.925 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the inauguration, about how many
electoral
votes that he had.

29:53.959 --> 29:54.926 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
AL GORE: Yes.

29:54.960 --> 29:56.561 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Yes.

29:56.595 --> 29:59.965 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, why is he not
part of your
focus, a main part of your
focus?

29:59.998 --> 30:02.467 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
AL GORE: Well, he is, and I
don't defend any
of that.

30:02.501 --> 30:08.807 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I just think that a much more
important part
of the problem we face, which
was evident

30:08.840 --> 30:15.847 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
10 years ago and is even more
evident now,
is that the way we share
information among

30:15.881 --> 30:21.253 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ourselves as American citizens
has been radically
transformed.

30:21.286 --> 30:28.260 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We don't have -- the line
between news and
entertainment has almost
dissolved, where

30:28.293 --> 30:33.865 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ratings now have a big impact on
what kinds
of stories are covered and not
stories.

30:33.899 --> 30:41.273 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And when you talk about
President Trump, the
cable networks turned over so
many hours of

30:41.306 --> 30:43.775 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
prime time to him.

30:43.809 --> 30:45.110 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Why?

30:45.143 --> 30:49.247 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Because he was entertaining, but
also because
it drove ratings.

30:49.281 --> 30:55.554 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And that is different from what
the news media
is supposed to focus on.

30:55.587 --> 30:59.458 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: But how much
responsibility
does he bear for what's going
on?

30:59.491 --> 31:06.565 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
AL GORE: Well, I mean, I think
that asserting
that former President Obama
wasn't born in

31:06.598 --> 31:10.702 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the United States was just the
height of irresponsibility,
of course.

31:10.736 --> 31:12.337 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And he corrected that one.

31:12.370 --> 31:14.172 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
There are others that have yet
to be corrected.

31:14.206 --> 31:18.043 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: You met with
President Trump
during the transition in New
York, and you

31:18.076 --> 31:24.249 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
have written about -- you have
said you have
been in touch with him since
then.

31:24.282 --> 31:25.383 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
What's your take on him?

31:25.417 --> 31:27.652 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
AL GORE: Well, what is the Latin
phrase, sui
generis?

31:27.686 --> 31:29.121 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
He's one of a kind.

31:29.154 --> 31:30.889 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

31:30.922 --> 31:35.527 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
AL GORE: I think -- like a lot
of people,
I'm still trying to figure out
exactly what

31:35.560 --> 31:38.296 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
he represents in American
politics.

31:38.330 --> 31:46.838 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
But, if nothing else, he
represents a way
for tens of millions of people
who were desperate

31:46.872 --> 31:52.811 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
for change to just turn the
table over and
say, we want to start over
again.

31:52.844 --> 31:55.313 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But it is a challenge for our
democracy.

31:55.347 --> 31:57.048 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It definitely is.

31:57.082 --> 32:06.391 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, again, the remedy has to be
devoting
enough attention to restoring
the way we make

32:06.424 --> 32:08.393 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
collective decisions in this
country.

32:08.426 --> 32:12.864 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And you're saying
that can
be done with a -- even with a
president like

32:12.898 --> 32:18.170 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Donald Trump, who is as
outspoken as he is
and who makes the controversial
statements

32:18.203 --> 32:19.171 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
that he does?

32:19.204 --> 32:21.006 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
AL GORE: I hope so.

32:21.039 --> 32:26.511 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We're less than two months into
this experiment,
and people are already reaching
conclusions.

32:26.545 --> 32:36.955 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, you know, George Orwell
once wrote that
a false belief sooner or later
collides with

32:36.988 --> 32:40.592 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
physical reality, usually on a
battlefield.

32:40.625 --> 32:45.697 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That's what happened with the
invasion of
Iraq, and we're still bogged
down there.

32:45.730 --> 32:52.070 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That is what would happen if the
Congress
passed this pending health care
bill that

32:52.103 --> 32:57.108 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
would knock so many millions of
people out
of coverage and raise the
expenses of so many

32:57.142 --> 32:58.677 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
others.

32:58.710 --> 33:05.016 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That's a physical reality that
can't be finessed
with words and falsehoods.

33:05.050 --> 33:08.620 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: What is your take
on the man
the president chose to head the
Environmental

33:08.653 --> 33:14.292 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Protection Agency, Scott Pruitt,
who, by the
way, just last week said he
doesn't agree

33:14.326 --> 33:17.863 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that carbon dioxide is a primary
contributor
to climate change?

33:17.896 --> 33:18.864 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

33:18.897 --> 33:20.765 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
AL GORE: I know.

33:20.799 --> 33:23.201 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that's a perfect example of
the problem
that I'm describing in "The
Assault on Reason."

33:23.235 --> 33:30.108 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Again, at some point, a false
belief collides
with physical reality.

33:30.141 --> 33:34.212 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We are seeing every night on the
television
news now a nature hike through
the Book of

33:34.246 --> 33:36.014 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Revelation.

33:36.047 --> 33:41.920 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
These climate-related extreme
weather events
have convinced the vast majority
of people

33:41.953 --> 33:45.056 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that the scientists have been
right for a
long time.

33:45.090 --> 33:46.825 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
We have to address this.

33:46.858 --> 33:54.199 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But putting someone in the EPA
who denies
even the most basic scientific
truth about

33:54.232 --> 33:59.404 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
this, you know, it's -- the old
cliches are,
you can say the Earth is flat,
but it doesn't

33:59.437 --> 34:01.239 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
