The Cook Political

35:46.111 --> 35:47.078 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Report.

35:47.112 --> 35:49.014 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Welcome to both of you.

35:49.047 --> 35:51.583 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And before we talk about health
care, I have
to ask you, Amy, about what
former Vice President

35:51.616 --> 35:57.088 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Al Gore said, trying to be
optimistic about
the ability of the news media
to, in his words,

35:57.122 --> 36:02.027 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
get the truth out of there in
the face of
a lot of, frankly, nontruths
floating around.

36:02.060 --> 36:03.928 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
AMY WALTER, The Cook Political
Report: Right.

36:03.962 --> 36:09.667 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Well, and we have created a
world now, us
as Americans, where we like to
surround ourselves

36:09.701 --> 36:14.806 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
with news and information that
already confirms
our own bias.

36:14.839 --> 36:20.278 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It is very uncomfortable for us
to go outside
of that circle, and we do it not
just in the

36:20.311 --> 36:23.415 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
channels that we choose, but in
the ways in
which we choose to get it.

36:23.448 --> 36:24.549 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Who are we following on
Facebook?

36:24.582 --> 36:26.217 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Who are we following on Twitter?

36:26.251 --> 36:28.086 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Usually, people who agree with
us.

36:28.119 --> 36:34.325 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so we call something fake
news because
it challenge us our assumptions,
rather than

36:34.359 --> 36:38.963 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
