that the issue
is not how many people are
covered, but whether

38:06.417 --> 38:08.286 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
they have access to that
coverage.

38:08.319 --> 38:12.957 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so you have a populist
president who promised
that everything was going to be
OK, we're

38:12.991 --> 38:15.426 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
not going to touch Medicaid,
we're not going
to touch entitlements, you are
going to be

38:15.460 --> 38:20.064 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
able to get everything, but it
is going to
be cheaper and better, and a
free market Republican

38:20.098 --> 38:24.969 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
leadership who says, no, we
never promised
those things, we think that the
market can

38:25.003 --> 38:26.804 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
take care of it.

38:26.838 --> 38:30.975 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, those two things are going
to continue
to collide, regardless of what
the CBO report

38:31.009 --> 38:32.744 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
says, and then we will see it in
a bill.

38:32.777 --> 38:35.013 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: How do you see
the political
impact of this, Tam?

38:35.046 --> 38:39.484 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TAMARA KEITH: Well, certainly
leading into
it, the Trump administration and
some in Congress

38:39.517 --> 38:45.557 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
were sort of trying to work the
refs, trying
to discredit the report before
it ever came

38:45.590 --> 38:47.258 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
out.

38:47.292 --> 38:52.163 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But these numbers are stark, you
